This recipe is fine as is but now I know what changes I will make to it next time. Using less sugar I'll need to increase the liquid so I'll try to add 1/4c. of s. cream along with the milk. I'd also use cake flour for a finer crumb. Rather than increase the zest for more tartness I added 1/2t. lemon oil to the batter and used less sugar in the glaze. I would definitely apply the glaze when the cake is fairly warm so that it will be absorbed throughout the cake. With these tweaks it should taste pretty close to the citrus bread they sell at Peet's Coffee.

