Rating: 4
This recipe is almost exactly like the one that Bernard Clayton has in his classic "The Complete Book of Breads." He adds a tablespoon of lemon extract to the batter, and peels the lemon rind with a vegetable peeler, then chops it for a chewier texture. I use only a teaspoon of lemon extract or 1/2 teaspoon of lemon oil, into the batter. Makes it super lemony.

