Rating: 4
Yum! I made some changes to this to make it healthier and it was a great success. I replaced the butter with 1/2 cup vegetable oil and cut the sugar back to 1 cup total-- 2/3 cup for bread and 1/3 cup for glaze. It was still very sweet and moist. Oil can almost always be subbed for butter in quick breads. The fats in oil are much healthier than the fats in butter. Instead of whole milk I used 1/4 cup low fat soy milk and 1/4 low fat yogurt. I also doubled the amount of lemon juice and zest and added 2 tbsp chopped fresh lavender flowers. I did as another reviewer suggested and poked holes all over the warm bread with a long skewer. Excellent suggestion. All the reviews for this recipe and for the "lemon tea bread" also on this site were very helpful in making this recipe fabulous. Thanks!

