Wonderful! Based on other reviewers recommendations, I increased the lemon zest in the batter to 3 tablespoons. I also added about 2 tablespoons of lemon juice to the batter. Baked it for 55 minutes. While it was still hot, I poked holes throughout the bread with a skewer and poured the lemon glaze over the top. I used powdered sugar with lemon juice to make the glaze rather than granulated sugar. The glaze soaked into the holes and made it super-moist. I wrapped it well in saran wrap and brought it to work the next day - still moist!

