Rating: 3
This was a really nice surprise. I have always liked lemony things, but often find that they're too sweet. This has a really nice balance and makes a great bread (more like a pound cake consistency) to have with tea or coffee. As for being too lemony, the nice thing about this is that you are completely in control of how lemony is. The actual tartness of the lemon doesn't come from the cake itself (I agree that a little lemon juice might be nice in the batter), but from the glaze. How lemony the cake is entirely depends on how much of the glaze you use. If you want it to be light, glaze lightly. This was a big hit at work, too, and SO easy to make. Five minutes and it was in the oven.

